author: brane
msg: Fix the build generator to link with the correct version of the BDB library,
and do some refactoring and cleanups.
* build/generator/gen_win.py (WinGeneratorBase.parse_options): Change the
logic for parsing the --with-httpd option (in preparation for other
options), and allow the argument to be a relative path.
(get_win_libs): Accept an 'cfg' parameter that defines the config name,
and tweak the name of the BDB library accordingly.
* build/generator/gen_msvc_dsp.py (Generator.write_project): Generate
dependent libraries based on the config name.
* build/generator/msvc_dsp.ezt: Take dependent libraries from the config
object, not from the global data.
* build/generator/gen_vcnet_vcproj.py (Generator.write_project): Renamed from
writeProject, for consistency with gen_msvc_dsp.py. Remove the logic that
selected the BDB library name based on the configuration, that's done
by get_win_libs now (see above).
Rename all 'target_ob' to 'target', for consistency with gen_msvc_dsp.py.
